The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, January 01, 2003 				 Arafat fears Israeli attack
																								Ramallah, Dec. 31 (Reuters): Palestinian President Yasser Arafat said today he feared Israel might exploit a possible US war on Iraq to escalate its own military attacks against Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza Strip.																								Speaking at a rally in Ramallah to mark the 1965 founding of his Fatah faction, Arafat also said Palestinians extended a hand for peace with Israel and welcomed a recent call by international mediators for a truce.																								He reiterated his opposition to attacks on Israeli and Palestinian civilians in an uprising against occupation in which at least 1,755 Palestinians and 675 Israelis have been killed.
